<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some of the mergers-and-acquisitions advisory =
business involves rigorous financial analysis, hard-nosed negotiation, deep=
 knowledge of financing markets and regulatory regimes, nuanced understandi=
ng of executive personalities and corporate cultures, accumulated wisdom an=
d personal charisma. But some of it involves, like, you get a list of compa=
nies, you make 100 educated guesses about companies that might want to sell=
, you make five educated guesses about who might want to buy each of them, =
you write 600 polite and analytical coldish emails saying =E2=80=9Chey let=
=E2=80=99s talk about selling you to X=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Clet=E2=80=99s t=
alk about you buying Y=E2=80=9D or whatever, and you see what you get. And=
=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>part of the job, a computer can do just so much fa=
ster than you can. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/31501912.257434/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMj=
MtMDUtMTUvamFwYW4tcy1hZ2luZy1wb3B1bGF0aW9uLWhlbHBzLXRoaXMteW91bmctZm91bmRlc=
i1hcHByb2FjaC1iaWxsaW9uYWlyZS1zdGF0dXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUxNjIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYm=
dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNTE2JnV=
0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd2a4a59c" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
